sentence: Malvern, PA-based real estate investment trust ("REIT") - Liberty Property TrustLPT - has leased two of its vacant industrial facilities covering an area of 1.3 million square feet.
The facilities are located in Chicago and Arizona.

Specifically, Liberty Property has leased 723,291 square feet of space at 1070 Windham Parkway in Romeoville, IL, effective from May 1 and 593,600 square feet at Liberty Logistics Center I, 563 S. 63rdAvenue, Phoenix, AZ, beginning Sep 15.
Liberty Property specifically focuses on metro-office, multi-tenant industrial and flex properties in the U.S. markets that have strong demographic and economic fundamentals.
The company also owns certain assets in the United Kingdom.
We believe that amid an improving U.S. industrial market, Liberty Property will experience growing demand for its industrial assets.
Moreover, leasing of the vacant spaces reflects growing demand for the company's space, ensuring steady revenue from these properties.
As a matter of fact, Liberty Property's portfolio comprises over 750 properties spanning 106 million square feet, and its tenant roaster includes 1,900 names.
Several industry bellwethers like Amazon.com Inc. AMZN , Kellogg Company K and The Home Depot, Inc. HD feature in its tenant list, which promise steady rental revenue for the company, going forward.
However, with recovery in the industrial markets going on for a long time, the chances of any striking decrease in availability rates are less.
Also, large construction pipeline increases the company's operational risks and an anticipated rise in interest rates remains a concern.
